;; it starts off with zero
;; it compares the first of the seq with its number
;; if the seq is empty, return the seq
;; if the seq is not empty, then:
;; if the first of the seq is less than or equal to the supplied number,
;; call the function again with the supplied number and the rest of the seq
;; if the first of the seq is greater than the supplied number
;; call the function again with the first of the seq and the rest of the seq
;; e.g.: (get-max 0 '(0 1 3 2 4 1))
;; then: (get-max (bigger-of-two 0 (first '(0 1 3 2 4 1)) (rest '(0 1 3 2 4 1))

;; then: (get-max (bigger-of-two 3 (first '(4 1)) (rest '(4 1))
;; then: (get-max (bigger-of-two 4 (first '(1)) (rest '(1))

    (cond
      (empty? coll) v
      (> (first coll) v) (apply mymax (first coll) (rest coll))
      :else (apply mymax v (rest coll))))

(fn [& n] (loop [s n acc (first n)]
   (if (empty? s)
     acc
     (recur (rest s) 
            (if (> (first s) acc)
              (first s)
              acc)))))

(fn [& lista]
      (loop [lst lista
             item (first lst)
             maior item]

              (if (seq lst)
                (if (< item maior)
                  (recur (rest lst) (first (rest lst)) maior)
                  (recur (rest lst) (first (rest lst)) item))
                maior)))

(fn [& s]
  (loop [s s, m 0]
    (if (seq s)
      (if (> (first s) m)
        (recur (rest s) (first s))
        (recur (rest s) m))
      m)))

(fn my-max
  ([x] x)
  ([x y] (if (> x y) x y))
  ([x y & more] (reduce my-max (my-max x y) more)))

(fn mx [& xs]
  (if (= (count xs) 1)
    (first xs)
    (let [y (first xs)
          ys (rest xs)
          z (apply mx ys)]
      (cond
        (> y z) y
        :else z))))

(fn [& params]
  "Returns the maximum value of a coll"
  (loop [coll params, max-value (first coll)]
    (if (empty? coll)
      max-value
      (recur (rest coll) (if (> max-value (first coll))
                           max-value
                           (first coll))))))
(fn stronger-list [& args] (reduce (fn stronger [x y] (if (> x y) x y)) args))

(fn max-value [& more]
  (loop [largest (first more)
         coll (rest more)]
    (if (empty? coll)
      largest
      (if (< largest (first coll))
        (recur (first coll) (rest coll))
        (recur largest (rest coll))))))

(fn my-ma [& num]
  (let [x (sort num)]
    (last x)))

(fn [& nums]
  (loop [mx (first nums) lst (rest nums)]
  (if (empty? lst)
    mx
    (if (> (first lst) mx)
      (recur (first lst) (rest lst))
      (recur mx (rest lst))))))

(fn [& coll]
  (loop [maxx -1
         coll coll]
    (if (empty? coll)
      maxx
      (if (> (first coll) maxx) 
        (recur (first coll) (rest coll))
        (recur maxx (rest coll))))))

(fn [v & args]
  (loop [maxv v
       	 [nextv & args] args]
    (cond
     (nil? nextv) maxv
     (> nextv maxv) (recur nextv args)
     :else (recur maxv args))))

(fn [& xs]
  (loop [m (first xs) xs (rest xs)]
    (if (empty? xs)
      m
      (if (> m (first xs))
        (recur m (rest xs))
        (recur (first xs) (rest xs))))))
(fn [x & rest] (reduce (fn [m x] (if (> x m) x m)) x rest))
